## NOTES FOR AI — CURRENT SESSION

- African names only. No Arabic names.
- The wrong approaches must feel competent and reasonable before they fail.
- Gate register and mirror behaviour must be shown for all three wrong approaches:
  - Executor: Register 1 throughout. Mirror emphasises the obvious pattern — makes it cleaner, more distinct than the solver left it. One element outside the pattern is present but not receding.
  - System builder: Register flickers false 3, never holds. Mirror shows the method's structure — everything categorised, ordered. The categorisation is perfect. The gate is elsewhere.
  - Information gatherer: Register 1, undisturbed — as if solver not yet present. Mirror gives complete data. Room is still. The catalogue is the mirror.
  - After sitting down: Register 2. Something that was background becomes foreground. The mirror shows what was always there.
  - After right question forms: Register 3 before solver acts. Gate confirms.
- Mirror prose rule for Chapter 1: describe the room's arrangement. Never state what it is showing. The reader holds the question.
- Do not name the operation in Chapter 1. Experience only. The name "what is missing" may appear at the very end, once, in narrator voice, after the ordinary life echo lands.
- The fourth wall never breaks. No direct address to reader.
- The sitting down must be preceded by exhaustion of all three wrong approaches.
- The solution after the right question arrives is fast and quiet. The gate closes without ceremony.
- Mystery person notebook format: Gate grade. Approach type. Mirror content (one precise physical description). Underlined: the gap the mirror showed. Register log time-stamped. Nothing else.
- Ordinary life echo: same question applied to ordinary work problem. Never labelled as connected. At least one other person in the scene goes still or the conversation changes register when the right question forms. Never explained.
- Chapter length: 2000-3000 words.
